Proposal title: Nouns Fund Education: Rebuild a Ugandan village Community School into a Nouns School
TLDR: Transform Ndurumo Primary School in Uganda into a modern, Nounish School. The project includes 4 classrooms, a community water source, administration and staff rooms, teacher's quarters, a playground, kitchen, and modern plumbing facilities, employing green technologies like solar energy and biogas. An alumni of the school, Davin Oyesigye, leads the project, which will also create a documentary to showcase the process and impact. The budget is allocated for planning, construction, project management, and media documentation, with funds managed by a 3/5 multisig wallet. Nouns DAO Africa's involvement extends to other community activities in Africa, promoting Nouns and crypto usage.

TLDR: Resubmission of Proposal 472 due to limitation of the timelock

Proposal title: Nouns Online: Proliferating Noggles to 22 million followers
TLDR: Rebrand Kungarna as 'Nouns Online,' a gaming, streaming, and content creation brand, offering Nouns DAO a 20% ownership and profit share. The plan includes leveraging Kungarna's reach (32.2 million fans, 2.7 billion views) to proliferate Nouns, with activities like rebranding, influencer collaborations, gaming events, and a dedicated Nouns Online House. Expected outcomes include significant impressions, expansion of the Nouns ecosystem, and various collaborative projects. The budget covers charity, events, operational costs, and creator support, with a proposed quarterly payment schedule.

Upgrade the data contract in Nouns V3 to fix two issues: eliminating a candidate creation fee charged during proposal updates and enforcing a transaction limit to match DAO rules. The upgrade, detailed in a pull request and reviewed by solimander, addresses a bug in charging fees for updating onchain proposals and a user experience issue with transaction limits on candidates. As the changes affect a side contract not directly linked to the core Nouns contracts, no official audit is planned. The transaction will update the data contract proxy implementation to the new version. The proposal is submitted by the verbs team.

Upgrade the Nouns Name Service (NNS) into an open protocol, sharing 95% of minting revenue with the Nouniverse. Plans include integrating Ecosystem and Referral Rewards, launching Community Level Domains, developing a nounish physical debit card, and expanding the NOGS token use cases. Achievements include NNS becoming the 3rd largest nounish project by holders and generating $190k organically. The funding covers core team operations, additional development, design, and marketing for six months. The proposal aims to connect the Nouniverse, empower communities, and promote proliferation.

6-8 months to expand Nouns' physical and digital presence. Achievements include cc0-lib.wtf development, a zine, and Prop House rounds. Plans include local activations, collaborations with artists outside Web3, hosting nounish events, producing merchandise, and distributing nounish kits to nonprofits. The proposal also involves printing 1,500 zines for community proliferation, with proceeds supporting production of future issues. The team, including Voadz and Nero One, will manage design, data, operations, and engage with charitable organizations for broader community impact.

Proposal title: Endaoment <> Nouns: Streaming Donations to the Global Nonprofit Ecosystem
TLDR: 120 ETH stream from the Nouns Treasury over 10 years to fund their Universal Impact Pool (UIP), leveraging Quadratic Funding to match donations to nonprofits onchain. This plan aims to mobilize a modest 1.44% of Nouns' current Treasury to globally impact thousands of nonprofits, encouraging broader community donations. Endaoment has already handled over $59 million in onchain donations. The UIP, with existing funds from other donors, allows for transparent, onchain donations to a wide range of compliant nonprofits. Adjustments to the contribution can be proposed if needed. This initiative aligns with Nouns  values of supporting public goods and decentralized community action.

6 months to develop the Nouns SDK, developer tools, dashboards, a Nounish event feed Discord bot, marketing, and developer community initiatives. Key goals include updating Nouns DAO features, enabling contract interaction, integrating Prop House and Snapshot events, enhancing the Discord bot, and creating extensive documentation and a developer portal. The budget includes development, marketing, competitions, and retroactive work funding. Stretch goals involve media handling for Nouns art and documentation of Nounish DAOs.

The Prop House team requests $63k monthly for 12 months to scale participant engagement in Nouns. Over the past year, they facilitated 200 rounds with $1M+ awarded, impacting over 50 communities. They introduced the on-chain Prop House protocol, meta transactions, on-chain voting, and audits. Future plans include enhancing round creation UX, supporting infinite rounds, protocol upgrades for L2s, new voting strategies, expanding round winners, and introducing a unique Nouns-related figure as an incentive. The goal is to bring more people on-chain and work towards sustainability by implementing fees on awarded assets. The total budget is $756k, with $45k/month for core team compensation, $15k/month for external contributions, and $3k/month for infrastructure and user cost subsidies.

Proposal title: Nouns Amigos or: How to Boost and Grow a Builders Community in Latam and Beyond
TLDR: Nouns Amigos, the Nouns community in Spanish, requests 120 ETH for six months to continue empowering builders and creators, particularly in Latin America. Their focus is on running Prop House and Amigo Infinite Rounds, fostering community engagement and development. They aim to maintain a trajectory of growth and diversification in the Nouns ecosystem by offering support and resources to Spanish-speaking builders. This includes hosting events, facilitating community activities, and providing a platform for innovation and building in native languages. The Amigo Squad will drive execution, ensuring the success of Prop House rounds and supporting community members in their builder journey.

Single Prop House round to award three Nouns to contributors who have significantly participated in Nouns DAO but do not own a Noun. This initiative aims to engage long-term aligned participants in governance. The round will have a one-week proposal submission period followed by a one-week voting period, open to all with basic spam-prevention criteria. Nouns DAO voters will conduct the voting, and the top three proposers will each receive a Noun, with the highest vote-getter choosing first. Nouns 862, 912, and 913 are suggested for this purpose. The Nouns will be held in escrow by martin, wag, and krel in a 2/3 safe. The round is tentatively scheduled to start in the first week of January.

Nouns Esports, a tier-one esports organization, is on a mission to disrupt the industry with a community and athletes-first approach. They have achieved significant success in Dota 2, Counter-Strike 2, Super Smash Bros. Melee, and Pokemon UNITE. The team now seeks to establish Nouns as a globally recognized brand in esports. Their plan includes continued top-tier competition, enhanced partnerships, in-game monetization opportunities, merchandise and product sales, and the innovative Nouns Esports Pass. They are requesting a budget of 2,098,600 USDC for 2024, aiming to cover player and coach salaries, support staff, operational expenses, and Prop House initiatives. The team, comprising various full-time staff and advisors, will manage operations using a multisig wallet. They also propose a commemorative mint to celebrate Nouns Esports' achievements.

Proposal title: Proliferating the Meme by Making Food a Public Good - Nouns Berries
TLDR: Addressing global food insecurity, the initiative aims to bring fresh produce to urban areas. They plan to develop aeroponic farming in Chicago, leveraging local policies and partnerships. The project includes creating an endowment for sustainable funding, avoiding future DAO requests. Long-term goals include federal grants, workforce development, and scaling through a non-profit-owned for-profit model. The proposal underscores the impact of nutritious food accessibility on public health and economic opportunity.

Proposal title: Nouns Gaming - Content Creator & Fortnite empire 2024
TLDR: Kungarna, a gaming brand, proposes rebranding to "Nouns Gaming" in 2024. With 32.2 million followers, they plan to increase coverage for the Nouns ecosystem. Targeting the growing gaming industry, they seek to become a global brand. Plans include retaining creators, expanding the roster, hosting gaming events, and collaborating with Nouns Esports. They request $793,000 for operations, events, and content creation, aiming to blend Kungarna's success with Nouns' vision for growth in gaming and esports.

Nouns.camp, developed by Obvious, Inc., is a Nouns governance client, facilitating over half of all votes in the ecosystem. It has successfully processed around 700 votes and numerous other on-chain actions. The platform, which averages about 100 daily visitors, now offers capabilities for creating proposals and candidates. Obvious, Inc., a company backed by investors including Y Combinator, is led by krel, olli, and prego, who are fully committed to Camp starting January 2024. Their proposal requests 50 ETH as retroactive funding for past development and a monthly funding of $33k USDC throughout 2024, totaling $396k USDC. This commitment aims to enhance Nouns governance and attract more users and builders to the platform.

Proposal title: Nouns Winter Shelter: Saving Cats & Dogs
TLDR: Nouns Shelter, led by Coral Ding, Sharon Liu, and Kiki Zhang, aims to proliferate the Nouns brand through animal welfare awareness in Beijing, China. The project, running from January to March 2024, plans to purchase and distribute pet food to Qiuqiu's shelter, which houses over 300 animals, and manufacture 300+ insulated Nouns Mini Shelters for stray animals. Supported by local celebrities and content creators, the initiative also includes a social media campaign and the creation of a documentary. The total budget is 39,850 USDC, covering food, shelters, content creation, and event logistics.

Proposal title: The Many Hats of Ben - a documentary about Benbodhi.⌐◨-◨ ✦₊ v2
TLDR: $22,160 for ashort documentary on Benbodhi, a Nouns DAO community member. First in a potential series spotlighting Nouns contributors. Adjustments from previous feedback include remote interviews and prioritizing online distribution, reducing the budget. Scheduled for late 2023 filming, completion by April 2024, the project aims to create CC0 content. This initiative, led by the "Non-fungible Aotearoa" team, is part of a larger plan to document Nouns community stories globally.

Proposal title: Gift a Noun to Nounish Founders: wiz
TLDR: Give 'wiz', founder of Wizards DAO, a Wizard noun. Wiz also created Federation.wtf, a cross-DAO governance platform, and Bound.wtf for NFTs linked to Nouns. Recognized for his significant contributions, including being a Nouns Gardener, wiz has played a pivotal role in expanding the Nouns community

Proposal title: Play Nouns: A Fun Game UI Layer to Keep Nouns Weird
TLDR: Seeks 22 ETH for a 3-month project to develop "Play Nouns,"a gamified frontend for Nouns DAO. This 8-bit style game includes governance participation, auction bidding, player profiles, chat, and mini-games, aimed at community engagement. The project, inspired by a community tweet, builds on existing Nouns assets. The roadmap involves game development, on-chain features, and multiplayer functionalities. Led by Yung Algorithm, a crypto and sound design expert, the demo is already live, showcasing the game's potential.

12-month extension. Achievements: Smooth Nouns Fork implementation, 100+ proposal candidates, proposal updates. Key works: Fork upgrade reconsideration, arbitrage mitigation, Nouns Governor and Client Incentives development. Future focus: Nouns Governor, Client incentives, L2 voting, private voting, Fork V2 upgrades. Compensation: $37.5k/month per person for 2 members, 1.5 ETH/month for solimander, totaling 900K USDC, 9 ETH. Regular 3-month updates. Payment via DAO-controlled streams, cancelable by proposal. Additional funding for audits, etc., requested separately.

$145,000 USDC + Noun 788 for NounSwap v1 & v2 development by Paperclip Labs. V1 allows Noun holders to swap with treasury Nouns via governance proposals. V2 aims for permissionless swaps, redemption tokens, and configurable fees. Budget: $42,000 + Noun 788 for v1, $88,000 for v2 (includes $15,000 for contract audits). Payment in milestones: $42,000 and Noun 788 now, $15,000 at audit, $88,000 post-v2 completion. Team includes experienced crypto product builders. Future plans involve improving swapping experience and maintaining the tool.

Proposal title: Nogglers - The Story Behind the Square Glasses
TLDR: Nogglers' animated series, centered on Noggles and 90s teens Steven and Will. Post-pilot, aims for broadcaster/streaming acquisition, no further DAO funds needed. Jux Animation Studio leads, with Marcello Laruccia (Animation Director), F bio Valle (Art Director), Guilherme Fleury (Lead Writer). Executive producers: TheBower, JP. 12-minute pilot in 5 months, updates on propdates. Budget for script, storyboard, sound, post-production, marketing. Marketing includes social media, PR, network outreach, YouTube partners, live-streamed event. Goal: sell series post-pilot.

Proposal title: Nouns Capture: Igniting Children's Worlds with Fun, Play, and Learning
TLDR: Nouns Capture' app aims to engage children with a Nouns-themed scavenger hunt. Includes Android development, global launch to schools, and curriculum integration. iOS MVP has 3522 downloads. The app teaches Web 3 concepts through Nouns collection from QR codes. Plans include UI upgrade, SubDAO integration, and reaching 20,000 PE teachers. Connected PE team will handle ongoing support. 4-month roadmap covers development, feature finalization, marketing, and launch. Budget allocated for UI, marketing, curriculum, and operations.

Proposal title: NounSwap: Swap Noun 933 for Noun 482 from the Noun Treasury
TLDR: Proposal to swap Noun 933 for Noun 482 from the Nouns DAO treasury. Reasons for swapping include aesthetic preference, trait alignment, and enhanced community engagement. Benefits to DAO: diversity in treasury, increased owner participation, and a dynamic treasury reflecting community trends. Swap facilitated by Paperclip Labs' tool, NounSwap, enabling easy proposal creation for treasury swaps without custody of Nouns.
